You are working in a service (bot) repository that must be deployed to a single VPS.

There is a separate infra repository already running on the server at /opt/infra:
- nginx reverse proxy is managed there
- HTTPS (certbot) is managed there
- shared docker network is called "edge"

This repository MUST:
- build and run its own container
- connect to the "edge" network
- expose an internal port (e.g. 8080)
- NOT expose ports to host (no "ports", only "expose")
- NOT manage nginx
- NOT manage SSL/certificates
- NOT modify /opt/infra

Goal:
Set up automatic deployment using GitHub Actions.

Target flow:
git push → GitHub Actions → SSH → VPS → deploy service

Implement the following:

1. Create or update docker-compose.yml:

- Service name: app
- Use build: .
- restart: unless-stopped
- expose port 8080 (or 80 depending on app)
- connect to external network "edge"
- set network alias: <service-name>-app
- DO NOT use container_name
- DO NOT publish ports

Example:

services:
  app:
    build: .
    restart: unless-stopped
    expose:
      - "8080"
    networks:
      edge:
        aliases:
          - SERVICE_NAME-app

networks:
  edge:
    external: true
    name: edge

2. Add GitHub Actions workflow:
.github/workflows/deploy.yml

It must:
- trigger on push to main
- connect via SSH using secrets:
  VPS_HOST, VPS_USER, VPS_PORT, VPS_SSH_KEY
- deploy into /opt/services/<service-name>

Deployment logic:

set -euo pipefail

SERVICE_NAME="REPLACE_SERVICE_NAME"
SERVICE_DIR="/opt/services/${SERVICE_NAME}"
REPO_URL="git@github.com:OWNER/REPO.git"

mkdir -p /opt/services

if [ ! -d "${SERVICE_DIR}/.git" ]; then
  rm -rf "${SERVICE_DIR}"
  git clone "${REPO_URL}" "${SERVICE_DIR}"
fi

cd "${SERVICE_DIR}"

git fetch --all --prune
git reset --hard origin/main

docker network inspect edge >/dev/null 2>&1 || docker network create edge

docker compose up -d --build
docker compose ps

3. Add docs/deploy.md explaining:
- service is deployed to /opt/services/<service-name>
- nginx/HTTPS handled in infra repo
- service must connect to edge network
- no ports should be exposed
- how to debug:
  docker ps
  docker compose logs -f
  docker network inspect edge

4. Important:
- Do NOT add Kubernetes, Swarm, Traefik, Ansible
- Do NOT handle SSL here
- Do NOT modify infra repo
- Keep setup minimal and production-safe

Replace:
- SERVICE_NAME
- OWNER/REPO

Ensure the docker network alias matches infra config:
UPSTREAM_HOST=<service-name>-app